ate wss: WebSocketServer;\n  private sessions: Map<string, DocumentSession> = new Map();\n  private clientDocMap: Map<WebSocket, { sessionId: string; clientId: string }> = new Map();\n  private db: DocumentDB;\n\n  constructor(server: Server, db: DocumentDB) {\n    this.db = db;\n    this.wss = new WebSocketServer({ server });\n    this.wss.on('connection', (ws: WebSocket, req: IncomingMessage) => {\n      this.handleConnection(ws, req);\n    });\n  }\n\n  private handleConnection(ws: WebSocket, req: IncomingMessage): void {\n    // Extract document ID from URL path: /ws/:documentId or /documents/:documentId/ws\n    const url = req.url || '';\n    const documentId = this.extractDocumentId(url);\n\n    if (!documentId) {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, {\n        type: 'error',\n        message: 'Invalid WebSocket path. Use /ws/:documentId or /documents/:documentId/ws',\n      });\n      ws.close(1008, 'Invalid path');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Verify document exists\n    const doc = this.db.getDocument(documentId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, {\n        type: 'error',\n        message: `Document ${documentId} not found`,\n      });\n      ws.close(1008, 'Document not found');\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const clientId = randomUUID();\n\n    // Get or create session for this document\n    const session = this.getOrCreateSession(documentId, doc.content);\n\n    // Register the client\n    session.clients.set(clientId, ws);\n    this.clientDocMap.set(ws, { sessionId: documentId, clientId });\n    this.db.addConnection(clientId, documentId);\n\n    // Send current document state\n    this.sendMessage(ws, {\n      type: 'sync',\n      content: session.content,\n      version: session.version,\n    });\n\n    // Handle incoming messages\n    ws.on('message', (data) => {\n      try {\n        const raw = data.toString();\n        let message: unknown;\n        try {\n          message = JSON.parse(raw);\n        } catch {\n          this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid JSON' });\n          return;\n        }\n        this.handleMessage(ws, clientId, session, message);\n      } catch (err) {\n        const errMsg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Unknown error';\n        this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: errMsg });\n      }\n    });\n\n    // Handle disconnect\n    ws.on('close', () => {\n      this.handleDisconnect(ws, clientId, session);\n    });\n\n    ws.on('error', () => {\n      this.handleDisconnect(ws, clientId, session);\n    });\n  }\n\n  private extractDocumentId(url: string): string | null {\n    // Remove query string\n    const path = url.split('?')[0];\n\n    // Match /ws/:id\n    let match = path.match(/^\\/ws\\/([^/]+)$/);\n    if (match) return match[1];\n\n    // Match /documents/:id/ws\n    match = path.match(/^\\/documents\\/([^/]+)\\/ws$/);\n    if (match) return match[1];\n\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  private getOrCreateSession(documentId: string, content: string): DocumentSession {\n    let session = this.sessions.get(documentId);\n    if (!session) {\n      // Load version history from DB to initialize the session\n      const latestVersion = this.db.getLatestVersion(documentId);\n\n      // Load operations from DB for the history\n      const dbVersions = this.db.getVersions(documentId);\n      const operations: Operation[] = [];\n      for (const v of dbVersions) {\n        if (v.operation) {\n          try {\n            operations.push(JSON.parse(v.operation));\n          } catch {\n            // Skip malformed operations in history\n          }\n        }\n      }\n\n      session = {\n        documentId,\n        content,\n        version: latestVersion,\n        operations,\n        clients: new Map(),\n      };\n      this.sessions.set(documentId, session);\n    }\n    return session;\n  }\n\n  private handleMessage(\n    ws: WebSocket,\n    clientId: string,\n    session: DocumentSession,\n    message: unknown\n  ): void {\n    if (!message || typeof message !== 'object') {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Invalid message format' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const msg = message as Record<string, unknown>;\n\n    if (msg.type !== 'operation') {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: `Unknown message type: ${String(msg.type)}` });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const opMsg = msg as unknown as ClientOperationMessage;\n\n    // Validate the operation object structure\n    if (!opMsg.operation || typeof opMsg.operation !== 'object') {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Missing or invalid operation' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    if (typeof opMsg.version !== 'number' || opMsg.version < 0) {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: 'Missing or invalid version' });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const op = opMsg.operation;\n\n    if (op.type !== 'insert' && op.type !== 'delete') {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: `Invalid operation type: ${String(op.type)}` });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Validate version is not in the future\n    if (opMsg.version > session.version) {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, {\n        type: 'error',\n        message: `Version ${opMsg.version} is ahead of server version ${session.version}`,\n      });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Transform the operation through history if it's based on an older version\n    let transformedOp: Operation | null = op;\n    if (opMsg.version < session.version) {\n      // Get all operations that happened since the client's version\n      const concurrentOps = session.operations.slice(opMsg.version);\n      transformedOp = transformThroughHistory(op, concurrentOps);\n    }\n\n    if (transformedOp === null) {\n      // Operation became a no-op after transformation (e.g., deleting already-deleted text)\n      session.version++;\n      this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'ack', version: session.version });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Validate the transformed operation against current document\n    const validationError = validateOperation(transformedOp, session.content.length);\n    if (validationError) {\n      this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'error', message: validationError });\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Apply the operation\n    session.content = applyOperation(session.content, transformedOp);\n    session.version++;\n    session.operations.push(transformedOp);\n\n    // Persist to database\n    this.db.updateDocumentContent(session.documentId, session.content);\n    this.db.addVersion(session.documentId, session.version, session.content, transformedOp);\n\n    // Send ack to the originating client\n    this.sendMessage(ws, { type: 'ack', version: session.version });\n\n    // Broadcast to all other clients\n    for (const [cid, clientWs] of session.clients) {\n      if (cid !== clientId && clientWs.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n        this.sendMessage(clientWs, {\n          type: 'operation',\n          operation: transformedOp,\n          version: session.version,\n          clientId,\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  private handleDisconnect(ws: WebSocket, clientId: string, session: DocumentSession): void {\n    session.clients.delete(clientId);\n    this.clientDocMap.delete(ws);\n    this.db.removeConnection(clientId);\n\n    // Clean up empty sessions\n    if (session.clients.size === 0) {\n      this.sessions.delete(session.documentId);\n    }\n  }\n\n  private sendMessage(ws: WebSocket, message: ServerMessage): void {\n    if (ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify(message));\n    }\n  }\n\n  closeAll(): void {\n    for (const [, session] of this.sessions) {\n      for (const [, ws] of session.clients) {\n        ws.close(1001, 'Server shutting down');\n      }\n    }\n    this.sessions.clear();\n    this.clientDocMap.clear();\n    this.wss.close();\n  }\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
